Recently renovated guest house in Old Havana, from where you can easily access by foot to many historical and cultural landmarks of the city.
 
Four private bedrooms each with private bathroom (two doubles, one twin and one triple). Each room enjoys air conditioning, WiFi, minibar, balconies (on the two double rooms), windows (on the remaining rooms), hot water 24 hours a day, lock on the doors, hair dryer, electric fans and safety deposit boxes. Daily cleaning is offered with no extra charge.
 
Shared area for dining and roof access with views across the city. Breakfast and other meals are offered by arrangement. As well as laundry, airport's taxi pick up and departure, parking and city walking trips.
 
 
Ideal for families, friends and couples, communication runs easy because the owners, Laura and Rodney, live at home. Laura is a young Architect that works from home with her husband, Rodney. Both of them speak fluent English.
 
